fields.title: Momo Hiari
fields.content:
Momo was born on November 9, 1996, in Kyotanabe, Kyoto, Japan. She initially gained attention through her appearance on the South Korean reality show "Sixteen," which was a competition to determine the members of the upcoming girl group that would later become Twice. Momo successfully made it to the final lineup and debuted as part of Twice under JYP Entertainment in 2015.

Known for her powerful and charismatic dance skills, Momo has contributed to the group's success with her performances in various music videos, stage performances, and television appearances. She is the main dancer of Twice, and her dance abilities have been showcased in many of the group's songs.

Twice quickly became one of the most popular and successful K-pop girl groups, gaining a massive fanbase both in South Korea and internationally. Momo, along with the other members of Twice, has been part of numerous albums, singles, and promotional activities, helping the group solidify their position in the K-pop industry.

fields.title: Wongyoung
fields.content:
From June 15 to August 31, 2018, Jang represented Starship Entertainment alongside An Yu-jin and Cho Ka-hyeon on the girl group survival reality television show Produce 48. She eventually placed first and debuted with Iz*One.[10]

Iz*One's Korean debut extended play (EP) Color*Iz was released on October 29, 2018, under the label Off the Record, with "La Vie en Rose" serving as lead single.[11] Both the EP and its lead single received immediate commercial success, leading the group to win the New Artist of the Year award at several shows, including Golden Disc Awards and Seoul Music Awards.[12]

The group's Japanese debut single, "Suki to Iwasetai", was released on February 6, 2019, under UMG's EMI Records subsidiary.[13] Along with the group's Japanese debut promotion, Jang was selected alongside the Japanese member Sakura Miyawaki to center a collaborative performance between Nogizaka46, Keyakizaka46 and AKB48 at the FNS Music Festival.[1
